Real photography goes in the subfolders here, not this root:

  hero/                              full-bleed hero backgrounds
  architecture/                      arches, courtyards, library/reading-room interiors
  experiences/                       dinner tables, salons, roundtable settings
  partners/                          partner/sponsor logos on neutral backgrounds
  events/cocktails-connections/      recap photos from that gathering
  events/women-and-wealth/           recap photos from that gathering
  events/financial-wellness/         recap photos from that gathering

Pass the resulting path (e.g. "/images/hero/courtyard.jpg") as the `src`
prop on components/ImagePlaceholder.js — it renders the real image in
place of the designed placeholder automatically. See that file's top
comment for the full photography direction (mood, color, and how people
should be represented).
